texts. Therefore, while technological solutions like anonymized evaluations or diversity algorithms can contribute positively, they should complement broader cultural shifts needed to challenge entrenched gender norms. In essence, closing the gender gap is not only a matter of justice but also enhances scientific rigor and creativity by embracing diverse experiences and viewpoints."
